news.title: Jaipur development body yet to apply for metro projects' loan
news.para: Urban development and housing (UDH) department officials had claimed that although there were no restrictions on JDA officials to forward files related to loans, they did not do that during the election period.

news.title: Crack down on hotels in Delhi extracting groundwater illegally: NGT
news.para: The Delhi Pollution Control Committee (DPCC) had earlier informed the tribunal that out of the 536 hotels, 257 were illegally extracting groundwater and 185 were doing so under a voluntary disclosure scheme.

news.title: In Pimpri Chinchwad, over 35% properties unregistered for tax
news.para: The Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) administration has outsourced the survey to an agency to assign a Unique Property Identification Code (UPIC), which will serve as a unique ID for all properties within the PCMC jurisdiction.

news.title: Maharashtra: Drone survey done, 18 lakh rural property cards on official website
news.para: A senior official from the state settlement commissioner’s office on Wednesday said 18.66 lakh property cards of rural residential land parcels had been uploaded and the remaining 50 lakh would be done by 2025.

news.title: Indore & Ujjain divisions see 3.5 lakh property sale registrations, log 11% growth
news.para: In Indore, income from property registrations in November decreased to Rs 171 crore from Rs 190 crore in October, shows data from revenue department.

news.title: NHSRCL to rent out 580,000 sq ft at Sabarmati multi-modal transit hub
news.para: The property, currently in the final stages of the request for proposal process, is planned to be leased out to a single lessee for a period of 35 years, extendable to another 35 years.

news.title: Maharashtra: Collectors told to finish RR rates talks with political leaders by Dec 31
news.para: The official said reports from the districts should reach the state stamps and revenue department by February. The final ready reckoner (RR) rates would be announced by March-end and they would be implemented from April 1.

news.title: NFRA bans two auditors for up to 10 years for lapses in DHFL's FY18 audits
news.para: In two separate orders, made public on Wednesday, the regulator has banned Jignesh Mehta for taking up audits for 10 years and Amit Vinay Chaturvedi for five years.

news.title: Muddy Waters is short Blackstone Mortgage Trust REIT
news.para: Carson Block, the CEO of Muddy Waters, told attendees at the Sohn Conference in London that Blackstone's real estate investment trust (REIT) faced issues of over supply, under-funded loan commitments, expiring leases and that its net operating income was compromised.

news.title: Chintels India reopens buyback option for Paradiso flatowners in five towers
news.para: ​Four balconies of Tower D collapsed on November 9. No casualty was reported in the incident as the tower was vacant and its surroundings cordoned off after a partial collapse of six floors claimed two lives in February 2022.

news.title: Brigade Group to jointly develop two lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: The project will have a developable area of around 0.20 million sq ft with a gross development value (GDV) of about Rs 500 crore.

news.title: Hindustan Construction Company sells 2.35 lakh sq meters land for Rs 95 crore
news.para: Hindustan Construction Company has sold the land parcel for Rs 95 crore to Oak and Stone Construction.

news.title: China Evergrande gets court notice regarding unit's $280 million recovery claim
news.para: The proceedings brought by unit Jinbi Property Management Company are related to the enforcement of Evergrande Property Services' deposit pledge of about 13.4 billion yuan.

news.title: Toronto home prices fall in November; down nearly 19% from 2022 peak
news.para: The seasonally adjusted average home price fell 2.2% in November from October to C$1,104,062 ($815,769), marking the fourth decline in the last five months.

news.title: Shree Cement plans to bid in India's lithium auction: Source
news.para: The move would be Shree Cement's first venture into mining and it has contacted Australia-based mining experts to work out details such as the premium that it should quote in its bid, the source added.

news.title: Two unauthorised colonies, labour quarters razed in Ludhiana
news.para: ​​These included an illegal colony being established at Star Road, Lohara; labour quarters being established in Jaspal Bangar area and another illegal under construction colony on Sua road, Giaspura.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance expects overall loan book to touch Rs one lakh crore in 3-4 years
news.para: The company is betting aggressively on the affordable home loan segment. "We started the affordable housing business a year back, and in the last 11 months we have reached loan book of Rs 1,000 crore," said Girish Kousgi, MD & CEO of PNB Housing Finance.

news.title: Veenu Gupta appointed as new Rajasthan RERA chairperson
news.para: ​After assuming charge, she said that emphasis will be laid on effectively implementing the provisions of the RERA Act.
